    The world may rage without,
    Quiet is here;
    Statesmen may toil and shout,
    Cynics may sneer;
    The great world, - let it go, -

    The world may rage without,
            Quiet is here;
    Statesmen may toil and shout,
            Cynics may sneer;
    The great world - l

    In the east a lightening;
    Where the woods are chill
    Moves an unseen finger,
    Wakes a sudden thrill;

    In my soul a glimmer,
